After his coup in 1992, Hazrat Ali chose Ahmad Shah Masood, the “Lion of the Panjshir.” It is little wonder that Ali and his brother-in-law, Rashid Dostum, tolerated Masood’s defiance, which eventually contributed to their fates. Afghanistan’s new revolution started with the courageous resistance against the communist dynasty, but it was doomed from the start.

Masood, who has been advised by the French president, had an impeccable life story unlike other modern Afghan leaders. He was a professional doctor and the son of a respected religious figure.
